%% Two-phase update: sequence diagram
%% Shows the temporal flow of a rule set update from the control
%% plane's perspective.

sequenceDiagram
    participant CP as Control Plane
    participant Compiler as Compiler Pipeline
    participant Delta as Delta Classifier
    participant Base as Base Classifier
    participant Root as Root Classifier Pointer
    participant Packets as Packet Path

    Note over CP,Packets: Phase 0: Steady State (single-tier)
    Packets->>Root: classify(pkt)
    Root->>Base: classify(pkt)
    Base-->>Packets: Fate

    Note over CP,Packets: Phase 1: Update Arrives
    CP->>Compiler: new_table = old_table.to_builder().push_rule(r).build()

    Note over Compiler: Diff old vs new table
    Compiler->>Compiler: changed_rules = diff(old_table, new_table)
    Compiler->>Compiler: k = changed_rules.len()

    alt k is small (delta strategy)
        Note over Compiler: Build delta from changed rules only
        Compiler->>Delta: compile(changed_rules) [O(k²)]
        Note over Compiler: Assemble two-tier Cascade
        Compiler->>Compiler: new_classifier = Cascade([Delta, Base])

        Note over CP,Packets: Phase 2: Atomic swap to two-tier
        Compiler->>Root: swap(new_classifier)
        Note over Root: ArcSwap::store / RCU publish

        Note over CP,Packets: Packets now see: Delta first, Base fallback
        Packets->>Root: classify(pkt)
        Root->>Delta: classify(pkt)
        alt Delta matches
            Delta-->>Packets: Fate (new rule)
        else Delta miss
            Delta->>Base: fall through
            Base-->>Packets: Fate (old rule)
        end

        Note over Compiler: Phase 3: Background merge
        Compiler->>Compiler: merged_table = merge(old_table, new_table)
        Compiler->>Compiler: new_base = compile_full(merged_table) [O(n²)]

        Note over CP,Packets: Phase 4: Swap to merged single-tier
        Compiler->>Root: swap(new_base)
        Note over Delta: Old two-tier classifier freed after readers drain

    else k is large (full rebuild strategy)
        Note over Compiler: Rebuild entire table
        Compiler->>Compiler: new_base = compile_full(new_table) [O(n²)]

        Note over CP,Packets: Phase 2: Atomic swap
        Compiler->>Root: swap(new_base)
        Note over Base: Old classifier freed after readers drain
    end

    Note over CP,Packets: Phase 5: Steady State (single-tier, updated)
    Packets->>Root: classify(pkt)
    Root->>Base: classify(pkt)
    Base-->>Packets: Fate
